[{"id":"skill-attestations-advisory-2#0","metadata":{"content":"The signed payload is the UTF-8 bytes of `origin + \"\\n\" + skill + \"\\n\" + tool_sha256 + \"\\n\" + signed_on + \"\\n\" + valid_until` with `origin` canonical (lowercase, no trailing slash, no default port) and `tool_sha256` lowercase hex. The gateway:","okf_concept":"skill-attestations-advisory-2","okf_type":"docs","title":"Skill attestations (advisory)"}},{"id":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-1#0","metadata":{"content":"Under a `## Skills` section, an executable skill is a normal markdown list item followed by an HTML comment carrying a JSON object with `version`, `tool` (path to the `tool.js`), and `tool_sha256` (hex SHA-256 of the `tool.js` bytes):","okf_concept":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"The executable-skill line in `llms.txt`"}},{"id":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-0#0","metadata":{"content":"> **Status: Draft v0.4, adopted.** This format is specified by the > [Executable Skills extension](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills/blob/master/docs/ext-executable-skills.md) > of the [llms-txt-skills](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills) > standard. This repo is its reference implementation; the spec and this code > are kept aligned (every MUST in the spec is field-","okf_concept":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"The executable-skill line in `llms.txt`"}},{"id":"why-1#0","metadata":{"content":"mcpwasm removes the trust requirement for the *code*:","okf_concept":"why-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"Why"}},{"id":"why-2#0","metadata":{"content":"- The tool runs in a separate QuickJS-wasm context with no host globals beyond what the host predefines (`registerTool`, `host`). No `fetch`, no `process`, no disk, no secrets. - The platform secret (e.g. a Stripe key) stays on the host side. The tool can only ask the host to perform a *named* internal action via `host.callInternal` (sync host) or a scoped `host.fetchOrigin` (async host). The host","okf_concept":"why-2","okf_type":"docs","title":"Why"}},{"id":"architecture-1#0","metadata":{"content":"- `host.mjs` â€” synchronous `ToolHost` (sync tools, `host.callInternal` capability). - `host-async.mjs` â€” `AsyncToolHost` (async handlers, `host.fetchOrigin` + the `extraCapabilities` mechanism that backs `host.memorySearch`, resource hardening). - `mcp-core.mjs` / `mcp-core-async.mjs` â€” JSON-RPC 2.0 MCP core (transport-agnostic). - `worker.mjs` â€” PoC MCP server (sync host, inline tools). - `worker","okf_concept":"architecture-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"Architecture"}},{"id":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-1#0","metadata":{"content":"A publisher that wants its skills to search over its own static content (docs, catalog text, any corpus) declares a memory snapshot with a single HTML comment **before** the `## Skills` section (this ordering is required by the reference parser):","okf_concept":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"Origin memory (search over static content)"}},{"id":"skill-attestations-advisory-0#0","metadata":{"content":"> Spec: [Skill Attestations v0.2](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills/blob/master/docs/ext-skill-attestations.md).","okf_concept":"skill-attestations-advisory-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"Skill attestations (advisory)"}},{"id":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-0#0","metadata":{"content":"**Static MCP: your tools are files, not servers.** Tools are published as static, hash-verified content and executed sandboxed on demand. What static site hosting did to web servers â€” \"don't run Apache, publish HTML\" â€” this does to MCP servers: don't run an MCP server, publish files. The publisher needs zero infrastructure; the MCP server is materialized per request from those files and evaporates","okf_concept":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"mcpwasm â€” Static MCP"}},{"id":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-0#0","metadata":{"content":"> Spec: *origin memory* in > [Executable Skills v0.4](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills/blob/master/docs/ext-executable-skills.md).","okf_concept":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"Origin memory (search over static content)"}},{"id":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-2#0","metadata":{"content":"- The `<!-- skill: {...} -->` comment marks the line as an *executable* skill. List items without it are treated as descriptive-only and ignored by the gateway. - `tool` is resolved relative to the origin. - `tool_sha256` is verified against the fetched `tool.js` bytes before the tool is loaded. Mismatch â†’ the skill is rejected (logged) and not registered. - If the JSON is invalid the line is sile","okf_concept":"the-executable-skill-line-in-llms-txt-2","okf_type":"docs","title":"The executable-skill line in `llms.txt`"}},{"id":"why-0#0","metadata":{"content":"MCP clients (Claude, Cursor, others) can call arbitrary tools. Running a third-party tool's code directly in your backend means that code can read your secrets, hit your DB, phone home, or loop forever. You either trust the author fully or you don't run the tool.","okf_concept":"why-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"Why"}},{"id":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-2#0","metadata":{"content":"``` <!-- skills-memory: {\"snapshot\":\"/skills-index.snapshot\",\"snapshot_sha256\":\"a0235f071aa7e28f2096312f22f1ad035901595f3fa91d2cc92b5879bbb7f6d5\",\"format\":\"minimemory-okf-v1\"} -->","okf_concept":"origin-memory-search-over-static-content-2","okf_type":"docs","title":"Origin memory (search over static content)"}},{"id":"skills-1#0","metadata":{"content":"The reference publisher is the docs-site (see \"Repository layout\"): it serves the spec snapshot and a `search_spec` skill that runs `host.memorySearch(args.q, k)` to do BM25 search over the four llms-txt-skills documents, plus `get_doc` and `list_docs`.","okf_concept":"skills-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"Skills"}},{"id":"architecture-0#0","metadata":{"content":"1. A publisher site ships `/llms.txt` plus per-skill `tool.js` and `SKILL.md` files. `llms.txt` lists each executable skill with a SHA-256 of its `tool.js`, and may declare an *origin memory* snapshot (see below). 2. On each request the gateway downloads `llms.txt`, parses the executable skills, downloads each `tool.js`, verifies SHA-256, and loads the verified ones into a fresh `AsyncToolHost` sc","okf_concept":"architecture-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"Architecture"}},{"id":"skill-attestations-advisory-1#0","metadata":{"content":"A publisher may serve a third trust ring â€” signed reviewer attestations â€” at `/.well-known/agent-skills/attestations.json`. Each entry is an Ed25519 signature over the canonical payload and has this shape:","okf_concept":"skill-attestations-advisory-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"Skill attestations (advisory)"}},{"id":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-2#0","metadata":{"content":"Think \"php-wasm, but for MCP tools\": the platform owner embeds the host, loads `tool.js` files, and each tool runs isolated in a QuickJS WebAssembly sandbox. The only bridge from the sandbox to the platform's internals is an explicit capability the host injects. No capability, no access.","okf_concept":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-2","okf_type":"docs","title":"mcpwasm â€” Static MCP"}},{"id":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-1#0","metadata":{"content":"mcpwasm is the reference implementation: a sandboxed runtime for third-party MCP tools (untrusted tool code inside QuickJS-wasm on Cloudflare Workers), plus a gateway that turns any static site publishing `llms.txt` with executable skills into an MCP server.","okf_concept":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-1","okf_type":"docs","title":"mcpwasm â€” Static MCP"}},{"id":"skills-0#0","metadata":{"content":"- `snapshot` is a path (relative to the origin) to a BM25 snapshot in the `minimemory-okf-v1` format (built by the [`@rckflr/minimemory`](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@rckflr/minimemory) engine; the wasm binary ships as `minimemory_bg.wasm`). - `snapshot_sha256` is the hex SHA-256 of the snapshot bytes. The gateway downloads the snapshot and **verifies it against this hash before injecting the ca","okf_concept":"skills-0","okf_type":"docs","title":"Skills"}},{"id":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-3#0","metadata":{"content":"This repo integrates with the [llms-txt-skills](https://github.com/MauricioPerera/llms-txt-skills) standard via two provisional extensions adopted in the spec: **executable skills** (v0.4, with *origin memory*) and **skill attestations** (v0.2). See the dedicated sections below.","okf_concept":"mcpwasm-static-mcp-3","okf_type":"docs","title":"mcpwasm â€” Static MCP"}}]